WEBVTT

00:04.047 --> 00:06.919
♪

00:09.966 --> 00:14.014
♪

00:23.545 --> 00:25.155
- You need to leave this house.

00:25.199 --> 00:26.809
What's wrong?

00:26.852 --> 00:28.637
- Get your husband
and meet me in the cellar.

00:28.680 --> 00:30.421
- I don't understand.

00:30.465 --> 00:32.641
- It's not safe here.

00:37.341 --> 00:39.082
- Oh, it wasn't--

00:39.126 --> 00:41.432
I--I wasn't feeling great
earlier.

00:41.476 --> 00:45.219
Catalina was just
checking on me.

00:45.262 --> 00:47.525
- I'm sorry to hear that.

00:47.569 --> 00:50.485
I take it this is
your first time?

00:52.269 --> 00:56.099
It's strange
in the beginning.

00:56.143 --> 00:59.146
But you'll
develop a knack for it.

00:59.189 --> 01:01.496
Just follow my lead.

01:04.325 --> 01:05.630
- Come on, everyone.

01:05.674 --> 01:07.458
Time for dessert.

01:09.852 --> 01:11.462
♪

01:11.506 --> 01:13.638
- Should have seen this guy...

01:14.813 --> 01:17.120
Rick.

01:19.296 --> 01:21.168
- Excuse me, pardon me.

01:21.211 --> 01:28.218
♪

01:29.959 --> 01:32.048
Let us out! Please!

01:33.484 --> 01:35.051
- Hey, quiet back there!

01:35.095 --> 01:37.271
God damn it.

01:37.314 --> 01:39.751
- That's my landlady
and her dickhead son.

01:39.795 --> 01:42.276
Year after year
they've raised my rent,

01:42.319 --> 01:44.147
so now it's time
for new management.

01:45.366 --> 01:46.541
- Never been
to the Carnival, kid?

01:46.584 --> 01:48.282
All kind of crazy shit.

01:48.325 --> 01:51.720
People dropping their savings
to live out some fantasy.

01:51.763 --> 01:53.678
And hey, if that's
what they want,

01:53.722 --> 01:55.941
folks like me will come in
and fill the void.

01:55.985 --> 01:57.508
- Same kind of folks
who got my sister.

01:57.552 --> 02:00.729
- That's the game, kid.
We don't make the rules.

02:00.772 --> 02:02.861
- Maybe the rules
need breaking.

02:02.905 --> 02:04.994
- Take that, you sick predator.

02:09.433 --> 02:11.435
Let us out!

02:11.479 --> 02:12.697
♪

02:12.741 --> 02:14.221
- I like you.

02:14.264 --> 02:16.701
You got heart.
I admire that.

02:16.745 --> 02:19.313
But that back there
is my business.

02:19.356 --> 02:21.141
And when you threaten
my business,

02:21.184 --> 02:24.492
you threaten my livelihood,
and I can't have that.

02:24.535 --> 02:26.711
You got me?

02:26.755 --> 02:29.497
- Yeah, I got you.

02:29.540 --> 02:31.542
We're good.

02:31.586 --> 02:33.457
Please!

02:33.501 --> 02:36.243
- I know what you're thinking,
soldier,

02:36.286 --> 02:41.161
and I'm telling you
to stand down.

02:41.204 --> 02:43.206
- And I say we're good.
- Please!

02:43.250 --> 02:46.209
- Just take me to the Carnival.

02:46.253 --> 02:48.255
- Yes, sir.

02:48.298 --> 02:55.305
♪

02:56.263 --> 02:57.481
- You should see
the other guy.

02:57.525 --> 02:59.222
- That's not funny, dumbass.

02:59.266 --> 03:01.529
You can't keep doing this.

03:01.572 --> 03:03.748
He had it coming.

03:03.792 --> 03:07.230
Because we're running out
of peas.

03:07.274 --> 03:08.753
- Yeah, these work better
'cause they adjust

03:08.797 --> 03:10.407
to your face.

03:10.451 --> 03:11.626
Shit.

03:11.669 --> 03:13.932
I can't get grounded again.

03:13.976 --> 03:15.412
I need you to tell them that

03:15.456 --> 03:16.805
I was defending your honor
or something.

03:16.848 --> 03:18.981
We already
used that last time.

03:19.024 --> 03:20.591
I'll--I'll think
of something else.

03:20.635 --> 03:23.594
- You're my favorite sister.
- You're an idiot.

03:27.337 --> 03:29.470
- Don't tell me that's Henry.

03:31.341 --> 03:33.517
Penelope, come on.
Really?

03:33.561 --> 03:35.084
- You don't even know him.

03:35.127 --> 03:36.564
- He sells dope
from the towers.

03:36.607 --> 03:37.826
- Well, I don't
need your permission.

03:37.869 --> 03:39.871
You're not Dad.

03:44.789 --> 03:47.270
No.
No.

03:47.314 --> 03:48.793
Help!

03:48.837 --> 03:50.360
Somebody help!
Please, get me away...

03:50.404 --> 03:51.883
- You're gonna burn!

03:51.927 --> 03:53.929
- Please!

03:53.972 --> 03:55.800
No!
Please, no!

03:55.844 --> 03:56.932
Stop!

03:56.975 --> 03:58.499
Let me go!

03:58.542 --> 03:59.848
No!

04:03.373 --> 04:04.896
- Please, no.

04:04.940 --> 04:06.594
Please, help me.

04:06.637 --> 04:08.248
Please.

04:08.291 --> 04:09.858
Henry, no!

04:09.901 --> 04:11.773
Please, no!
- Step right up!

04:11.816 --> 04:14.166
Step right up,
take your pick!

04:14.210 --> 04:15.820
♪

04:20.390 --> 04:22.087
Hurry up and join the fun!

04:22.131 --> 04:24.612
- I know this really isn't,
uh, my old apartment, but

04:24.655 --> 04:26.527
you know, it'll do, right?

04:28.920 --> 04:31.401
I actually--I rented this out
for the hour.

04:31.445 --> 04:33.838
I--I was actually planning
on somebody else...

04:33.882 --> 04:35.710
- Martyrs must...
- But I...

04:35.753 --> 04:37.189
I mean, look!

04:37.233 --> 04:39.104
The night, it--

04:39.148 --> 04:40.671
it brought us back together.

04:40.715 --> 04:42.282
Isn't...

04:44.240 --> 04:45.763
I found you.

04:56.905 --> 04:59.386
♪

05:02.476 --> 05:04.434
You know, I missed you.

05:04.478 --> 05:07.394
♪

05:07.437 --> 05:10.919
Did you miss me?

05:10.962 --> 05:13.051
No.
No, Henry.

05:13.095 --> 05:16.098
I said, did you miss me?

05:16.141 --> 05:18.405
- I'm not supposed to be here.

05:18.448 --> 05:20.320
I am not supposed to be here.

05:20.363 --> 05:22.365
Really, so where--

05:22.409 --> 05:24.802
where should you be?

05:31.026 --> 05:33.376
- There's so much that
I didn't get to tell you.

05:33.420 --> 05:35.204
- All martyrs must
be Purged tonight.

05:35.247 --> 05:37.032
No exceptions.

05:37.075 --> 05:39.295
- But now I can.

05:39.339 --> 05:42.211
- Go to Hell.

05:45.040 --> 05:46.955
Look around.

05:46.998 --> 05:53.788
♪

05:53.831 --> 05:56.399
This is Hell.

05:57.879 --> 06:01.622
- Shh, shh, it's okay.

06:01.665 --> 06:03.667
It's okay.

06:20.031 --> 06:22.251
- Come on, David.
Come on, come on.

06:22.294 --> 06:23.774
- The voicemail--

06:23.818 --> 06:27.343
- Oh, God.
This isn't happening.

06:29.650 --> 06:33.436
- No, I really
need to get going.

06:33.480 --> 06:35.612
My friend, he's--he's waiting
for me.

06:35.656 --> 06:37.092
- These things don't take long.

06:37.135 --> 06:38.789
We're good at what we do.
- Mm-hmm.

06:38.833 --> 06:40.617
- This friend
you keep mentioning.

06:40.661 --> 06:43.054
Is this a "friend" friend,
or a boyfriend?

06:43.098 --> 06:44.447
- He's not my boyfriend.

06:44.491 --> 06:47.102
- So,
it's a Purge Night booty call.

06:47.145 --> 06:48.712
- No, it's not like that.

06:48.756 --> 06:51.106
- Do you know that Purge Night
has the second highest

06:51.149 --> 06:53.804
conception rate of the year
after New Year's Eve?

06:53.848 --> 06:56.459
- Lot of people out there
with a screw loose, I guess.

06:56.503 --> 06:59.419
- Two of my kids were
conceived on Purge Night.

06:59.462 --> 07:01.464
- I--I didn't mean
to offend you.

07:01.508 --> 07:02.639
- I'm not offended.

07:02.683 --> 07:04.162
- We rescued Marge
three years ago.

07:04.206 --> 07:06.034
- Jesus, I'm so sorry.

07:06.077 --> 07:07.470
- Don't be.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.472
I've healed.

07:09.516 --> 07:12.475
I'm better.

07:12.519 --> 07:14.956
Hmm.
My ex

07:14.999 --> 07:17.045
Feel sorry
for that sack of shit.

07:17.088 --> 07:19.090
What happened?

07:19.134 --> 07:22.180
- Let's just say
we adjusted his attitude.

07:22.224 --> 07:24.095
And his face.

07:27.142 --> 07:33.148
♪

07:33.191 --> 07:35.542
- Marge can be
a little intense.

07:35.585 --> 07:38.022
- Her story is so awful.

07:38.066 --> 07:39.937
- But now she's stronger
for it.

07:39.981 --> 07:42.723
We're all survivors here.

07:42.766 --> 07:43.724
Including you.

07:43.767 --> 07:46.291
Don't forget that.

07:47.510 --> 07:49.207
- Thank you.

07:49.251 --> 07:51.166
Thank you all

07:51.209 --> 07:53.124
for being here tonight.

07:53.168 --> 07:54.865
But really,
where would you rather be?

07:56.171 --> 07:57.781
Seriously, as I look out

07:57.825 --> 08:00.480
at this remarkable crowd,

08:00.523 --> 08:02.482
I'm reminded
how fortunate I am.

08:02.525 --> 08:06.050
I mean, successes,
I've had a few.

08:07.269 --> 08:09.358
But I'd like to take a moment

08:09.401 --> 08:11.752
to cast the spotlight
on another wonderful

08:11.795 --> 08:14.537
achievement of my life:
my wife, Eleanor.

08:14.581 --> 08:16.713
- Aww.
- The real star of the evening.

08:16.757 --> 08:18.236
Yes.

08:18.280 --> 08:20.064
To Eleanor!

08:20.108 --> 08:22.502
She has worked tirelessly

08:22.545 --> 08:24.373
planning this party
to perfection,

08:24.416 --> 08:26.288
and tonight is a testament

08:26.331 --> 08:30.205
to her hard work
and dedication to our cause:

08:30.248 --> 08:33.121
replenishing the New Founding
Fathers' war chest.

08:33.164 --> 08:35.210
- Yes.
- That's right.

08:38.256 --> 08:41.390
We hold the keys to success.

08:41.433 --> 08:43.305
Seriously, I have them.
I'll show them to you later.

08:44.785 --> 08:47.048
We can make a difference.

08:47.091 --> 08:50.965
Because when
the NFFA thrives, we thrive.

08:51.008 --> 08:55.709
Now, as tribute
to a very successful year,

08:55.752 --> 08:59.147
we're spoiling you
with not one,

08:59.190 --> 09:01.105
not two,

09:01.149 --> 09:02.846
but three offerings.

09:09.549 --> 09:12.116
- Oh, boy.
- Yes.

09:12.160 --> 09:14.118
- We apologize,
they have not been

09:14.162 --> 09:15.990
sanitized for your protection.

09:18.906 --> 09:22.039
- Our staff will hand out
your weapons.

09:22.083 --> 09:24.520
Each one...

09:24.564 --> 09:28.785
has been hand-crafted.

09:28.829 --> 09:30.831
Blessed be America,

09:30.874 --> 09:32.615
a nation reborn.

09:32.659 --> 09:34.922
all: Blessed be us.

09:34.965 --> 09:37.707
A future more prosperous.

09:37.751 --> 09:40.014
Blessed be America,

09:40.057 --> 09:41.842
a nation reborn.

09:41.885 --> 09:44.671
A future more prosperous!

09:49.284 --> 09:51.373
- Hey.

09:51.416 --> 09:52.679
How'd you sleep?

09:52.722 --> 09:55.856
You dream about me?

09:57.161 --> 10:00.121
Don't touch me.

10:00.164 --> 10:03.341
- Okay, that's--

10:03.385 --> 10:05.300
that's the Penny I know.

10:05.343 --> 10:07.955
Always fighting.

10:07.998 --> 10:10.740
You know even--even when
I gave you a home.

10:10.784 --> 10:12.176
- You gave me drugs.

10:12.220 --> 10:14.004
You ruined my life
with that shit.

10:14.048 --> 10:16.267
- I gave you what you wanted.

10:16.311 --> 10:19.619
I let you live.
And what do you do?

10:19.662 --> 10:22.404
You break my heart so
you can join a fucking cult.

10:27.975 --> 10:29.237
What do you want
to listen to?

10:29.280 --> 10:30.673
- Whatever you want.
I don't know.

10:30.717 --> 10:33.284
- Come on, come on.
I'm taking requests.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.288
- Yeah, okay,
that narrows it down.

10:38.855 --> 10:41.292
[hip-hop music
plays quietly over speakers]

10:41.336 --> 10:43.251
You got this place
to yourself?

10:43.294 --> 10:45.340
- Yeah, yeah.
It's pretty sweet, right?

10:45.383 --> 10:47.342
- Yeah, it's sick.

10:47.385 --> 10:48.996
- Um...

10:49.039 --> 10:50.911
♪

10:52.869 --> 10:55.306
♪

10:55.350 --> 10:57.221
Is--are you--
are you cool with this?

10:57.265 --> 10:58.527
- Yeah, sure, totally.

10:58.570 --> 11:00.268
You want some?

11:00.311 --> 11:01.965
- Nah, I'm good.

11:02.009 --> 11:04.011
- You afraid your--
your big bro's gonna

11:04.054 --> 11:06.448
flip out on you or something?
- He knows I can handle myself.

11:06.491 --> 11:07.579
- No, yeah, I know.

11:07.623 --> 11:09.669
Miguel's right about that.

11:09.712 --> 11:11.888
But man, he's, like, so wired.

11:11.932 --> 11:14.282
I feel like you look
at him wrong for two seconds

11:14.325 --> 11:15.718
and he wants to kill you.

11:15.762 --> 11:17.067
- He's just angry.

11:17.111 --> 11:18.895
I get it.
So am I.

11:18.939 --> 11:20.070
- No, you're sad.

11:20.114 --> 11:22.290
There's a difference.

11:25.772 --> 11:27.948
- You don't know
what we've been through.

11:27.991 --> 11:32.692
♪

11:32.735 --> 11:34.868
- No, yeah, you're right.
Sorry.

11:34.911 --> 11:37.087
I--I don't.

11:37.131 --> 11:39.655
Yeah, I--I can't imagine.

11:39.699 --> 11:42.310
♪

11:42.353 --> 11:45.313
And, uh, I know it's not
really the same thing

11:45.356 --> 11:47.184
but, uh--

11:47.228 --> 11:49.621
but my parents are gone, too.

11:49.665 --> 11:51.493
- They're...

11:51.536 --> 11:53.713
- No, they--I mean,
they might as well be.

11:53.756 --> 11:55.018
They, uh...

11:55.062 --> 11:56.759
They got locked up

11:56.803 --> 11:59.414
trying to jack a grocery store.

12:01.329 --> 12:02.852
But I mean,
even if they do get out,

12:02.896 --> 12:07.770
I really don't want anything
to do with them.

12:07.814 --> 12:09.772
Got my own life, you know?

12:09.816 --> 12:12.732
I got--I got big plans.

12:12.775 --> 12:15.299
- Yeah, damn right.

12:15.343 --> 12:16.910
- I don't know.

12:16.953 --> 12:18.955
Like, I got places to see.

12:18.999 --> 12:20.957
I got things to do.

12:21.001 --> 12:23.743
- That narrows it down.

12:23.786 --> 12:25.440
♪

12:25.483 --> 12:27.355
Um, so,

12:27.398 --> 12:30.401
I got this book for Christmas

12:30.445 --> 12:33.230
when I was a kid,
and it has

12:33.274 --> 12:36.494
all the national parks
in the country.

12:36.538 --> 12:39.280
And so I'm gonna--
I'm gonna go to all of them.

12:39.323 --> 12:42.413
You should come with me.

12:42.457 --> 12:43.980
Sorry, I don't mean
like right now.

12:44.024 --> 12:45.112
- I don't.

12:45.155 --> 12:47.244
Um, don't worry about it.

12:47.288 --> 12:49.551
No, but I--I gotta save up
a little bit

12:49.594 --> 12:51.205
and then, uh--
and then I'm gonna go.

12:51.248 --> 12:53.468
I wanna kind of get
this big camper

12:53.511 --> 12:56.601
and just, like, jam it full
of food and just drive.

13:01.563 --> 13:03.608
♪

13:03.652 --> 13:06.263
You're really pretty.

13:06.307 --> 13:09.963
- Thank you.

13:10.006 --> 13:12.835
What's it like?

13:12.879 --> 13:14.532
That?
Oh, I don't--

13:16.621 --> 13:18.406
I don't, like,
do it that often.

13:18.449 --> 13:21.757
I just--every once in a while
to relax.

13:21.801 --> 13:24.238
Um, but, uh...

13:27.023 --> 13:31.898
I guess it just, uh, just kinda

13:31.941 --> 13:35.292
makes the edges
a little softer.

13:35.336 --> 13:41.255
♪

13:44.301 --> 13:46.086
♪

13:46.129 --> 13:47.609
It's okay.

13:49.132 --> 13:53.223
Once I Purge,
all this anger will be gone.

13:53.267 --> 13:57.358
I won't have to see you
in my head every night.

13:57.401 --> 14:00.230
And you can finally
stop fighting.

14:05.453 --> 14:08.412
- I hate you.
I hope you die.

14:12.939 --> 14:16.594
- You know, I never, uh,

14:16.638 --> 14:19.815
I never went
on that road trip

14:19.859 --> 14:21.295
to all those parks.

14:21.338 --> 14:23.253
I thought about it
after you left, but...

14:23.297 --> 14:25.516
- Maybe next year.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.476
I'll camp in Yosemite
and I can--

14:28.519 --> 14:32.001
I can sleep under the stars.

14:32.045 --> 14:35.178
And if it gets cold,

14:35.222 --> 14:36.832
I can build a fire.

14:48.148 --> 14:49.932
[upbeat country music
playing over radio]

14:49.976 --> 14:51.412
- Step right up!

14:51.455 --> 14:53.240
